        "duration": 1.521
    },
    {
        "text": "the n, and then if I multiply",
        "start": 729.6,
        "duration": 1.919
    },
    {
        "text": "x to the n by x I get one last term",
        "start": 731.519,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "which is x to the n plus 1.",
        "start": 733.839,
        "duration": 2.321
    },
    {
        "text": "And I've shifted them all along so that",
        "start": 736.16,
        "duration": 2.4
    },
    {
        "text": "you can see",
        "start": 738.56,
        "duration": 1.2
    },
    {
        "text": "that if I take one of these away from",
        "start": 739.76,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "the other",
        "start": 742.32,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "all these terms cancel, leaving me with",
        "start": 743.6,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "just the first term and the last term.",
        "start": 747.04,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "So in particular it turns out that Sn",
        "start": 749.76,
        "duration": 3.759
    },
    {
        "text": "into 1 minus x - so I've just taken the",
        "start": 753.519,
        "duration": 2.801
    },
    {
        "text": "second term from the first term -",
        "start": 756.32,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "equals, well, there's nothing to take away",
        "start": 758.88,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "from the 1.",
        "start": 761.44,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "They cancel, they cancel, they cancel;",
        "start": 763.44,
        "duration": 2.399
    },
    {
        "text": "everything cancels, that cancels and I'm",
        "start": 765.839,
        "duration": 1.841
    },
    {
        "text": "just left with that last term:",
        "start": 767.68,
        "duration": 2.159
    },
    {
        "text": "1 minus x to the n plus 1. Now",
        "start": 769.839,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "the series we've got is an infinite",
        "start": 772.959,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "series, this- this series ends after n",
        "start": 774.639,
        "duration": 1.921
    },
    {
        "text": "terms. This series goes on to infinity.",
        "start": 776.56,
        "duration": 3.279
    },
    {
        "text": "So what happens as n goes to infinity? Ss",
        "start": 779.839,
        "duration": 3.12
    },
    {
        "text": "n goes to infinity, because x is less",
        "start": 782.959,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "than 1, x",
        "start": 784.959,
        "duration": 1.041
    },
    {
        "text": "to the n plus 1 goes to zero. Imagine a",
        "start": 786.0,
        "duration": 2.639
    },
    {
        "text": "half. If I keep- a half times a half is a",
        "start": 788.639,
        "duration": 2.64
    },
    {
        "text": "quarter, times a half is an eighth, times",
        "start": 791.279,
        "duration": 2.081
    },
    {
        "text": "a half is a sixteenth - it just",
        "start": 793.36,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "gradually goes towards zero. So the x to",
        "start": 795.12,
        "duration": 2.719
    },
    {
        "text": "the n plus 1 goes to 0. \nWe're nearly there",
        "start": 797.839,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "Brady, hang in there.",
        "start": 801.6,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "So this means that S infinity is 1",
        "start": 802.88,
        "duration": 3.6
    },
    {
        "text": "over 1 minus x. So this sum",
        "start": 806.48,
        "duration": 3.68
    },
    {
        "text": "I can now do, because x is- I'm just",
        "start": 810.16,
        "duration": 2.799
    },
    {
        "text": "replacing x by",
        "start": 812.959,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "1 over q plus 1. This S infinity for",
        "start": 814.639,
        "duration": 2.961
    },
    {
        "text": "me becomes 1 over 1",
        "start": 817.6,
        "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
        "text": "minus 1 over q plus 1,",
        "start": 821.199,
        "duration": 3.601
    },
    {
        "text": "and that is equal to q plus 1",
        "start": 824.8,
        "duration": 3.279
    },
    {
        "text": "over q right? That's just rearranging\nthis.",
        "start": 828.079,
        "duration": 2.981
    },
    {
        "text": "So if I come back to the all-important",
        "start": 831.6,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "remainder, the rest, this thing here, that",
        "start": 834.8,
        "duration": 3.039
    },
    {
        "text": "I'm trying to bound,",
        "start": 837.839,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "remember I've said it - remember remember",
        "start": 839.839,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "remember - I've said it\nmust be an integer.",
        "start": 842.079,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "So the remainder, I've now- I know it has",
        "start": 844.639,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "to be less",
        "start": 846.959,
        "duration": 0.801
    },
    {
        "text": "than 1 over q plus 1",
        "start": 847.76,
        "duration": 3.519
    },
    {
        "text": "times by this sum, well this is this sum,",
        "start": 851.279,
        "duration": 3.761
    },
    {
        "text": "so it's times q plus 1 over q.",
        "start": 855.04,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "So the q plus 1s cancel. So this",
        "start": 858.48,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "is r must be less than 1 over q,",
        "start": 862.48,
        "duration": 3.2
    },
    {
        "text": "okay? Right we're nearly there now,",
        "start": 865.68,
        "duration": 2.24
    },
    {
        "text": "because we already know",
        "start": 867.92,
        "duration": 2.32
    },
    {
        "text": "that r has to be positive, because it's",
        "start": 870.24,
        "duration": 2.159
    },
    {
        "text": "just the sum of a positive- of positive",
        "start": 872.399,
        "duration": 2.081
    },
    {
        "text": "terms.",
        "start": 874.48,
        "duration": 1.039
    },
    {
        "text": "So r is greater than zero, which means",
        "start": 875.519,
        "duration": 4.0
    },
    {
        "text": "that this- for this proof to work",
        "start": 879.519,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "r is bounded between zero",
        "start": 882.959,
        "duration": 3.201
    },
    {
        "text": "and 1 upon q. But q is bigger than 1,",
        "start": 886.16,
        "duration": 4.32
    },
    {
        "text": "so this is a fraction less than 1 - i.e. r",
        "start": 890.48,
        "duration": 3.44
    },
    {
        "text": "is less than 1. Which means",
        "start": 893.92,
        "duration": 3.52
    },
    {
        "text": "it cannot be an integer. Therefore e",
        "start": 897.44,
        "duration": 2.72
    },
    {
        "text": "cannot be",
        "start": 900.16,
        "duration": 0.799
    },
    {
        "text": "represented as a rational number, so it",
        "start": 900.959,
        "duration": 2.56
    },
    {
        "text": "has to be irrational. Ta-da!",
